SIMPLE: interminable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interminable
<hw>In*ter"mi*na*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>interminabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>interminable</ets>. See
<er>Terminate</er>.]</ety> <def>Without termination; admitting no limit;
boundless; endless; wearisomely protracted; <as>as,
<ex>interminable</ex> space or duration; <ex>interminable</ex>
sufferings; an <ex>interminable</ex> sermon</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>That wild <qex>interminable</qex> waste of waves.</q>
<rj><qau>Grainger.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Boundless; endless; limitless; illimitable;
immeasurable; infinite; unbounded; unlimited.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interminableness</ent>⟦br⟧
